main event: A local civilian group observed three unidentified flying objects in the sky over Adana, Washington on September 25, 1959.
interesting points: The objects were round and had a blue cast,The first two objects were sighted before a third appeared,They flew in a south to southwest direction before disappearing to the southeast,The observation lasted about 10 minutes with an estimated velocity of 30-40 degrees,There were no sounds heard during the observation.
sighted object: three round objects with a blue cast
